author: @coreyms
text: If anyone would like to jump to a specific file format, here are the timestamps for the video: Read CSV - 0:56 Write CSV - 3:20 Write TSV - 4:40 Read TSV - 6:00 Write Excel - 6:15 Read Excel - 10:42 (Start at 6:15 to see installed packages) Write JSON - 12:18 Read JSON - 15:41 Write SQL - 16:59 Read SQL - 24:57 (Start at 16:59 to see installed packages)  Hope everyone is staying safe and healthy! I'm going to be taking a break from the Pandas series for a bit after this video. I'd like to cover some fun one-off videos where we can do some API coding. Suggestions are welcome. I might try to do a video on the YouTube API, Twitter, Reddit, and some others. Hope you're all having a great week!

Do you have any idea how to do this cleanly?  Thanks in advance for your help!

text: #24:57 Just in case: If you are using sqlite3 instead of sqlalchemy, you have to use SQL string not the table name:  #-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- import sqlite3 as sq3  conn=sq3.connect(my_path) #connecting to the database  sql_str='SELECT * FROM my_tbl_name'  sql_df=pd.read_sql_query(sql_str, conn) #-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- or you will get error: "Execution failed on sql..."  https://pandas.pydata.org/pandas-docs/stable/reference/api/pandas.read_sql_query.html
